# SCSS styles

## Source of truth

- Component styles: `src/components/<name>/<Name>.module.scss`
- Global styles: `src/styles/` (`globals.scss`, `_variables.scss`, `_fonts.scss`)
- Generated mirror: `public/css/` — **do not edit or commit** (gitignored). Next.js compiles `.module.scss` imports directly.

## Conventions

- Use CSS modules: `import styles from './Component.module.scss'`
- BEM-style class names (e.g. `weatherCard`, `weatherCard__main`, `weatherCard__label`)
- Shared tokens from `src/styles/_variables.scss` where applicable

## After editing

- `pnpm dev` recompiles SCSS automatically — no extra step needed for local preview.
- `pnpm build` runs `build-sass` then `next build`; the `public/css/` mirror is regenerated locally but not committed.
- Commit only the `.scss` file changes.
